docs.text: Hash Function A hash function is any funtion that can be used to map data of arbitrary size onto data of a fixed size. We use Hash function to implement Hash Table DJB2 Hash Function C++ 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8 unsinged long long djb2 ( char * str ) { unsigned long long hash = 5381 ; int c ; while (( c = * ( str ++ ))) { hash = ( hash << 5 ) + hash + c ; } return hash ; } code input: "hello world" output: 13876786532495509697
